# Voice-to-spec assistant (issue #43) — server-side only, never commit real values.
# Revised 2026-07-05: output is voice-in/text-out. No TTS, no ElevenLabs —
# that integration (api/tts.js, ELEVENLABS_API_KEY) has been removed.

# Get a key at https://console.groq.com — used by api/next-turn.js (picks
# the assistant's next question) and api/file-feedback.js (extracts the
# scope of work at session end).
GROQ_API_KEY=

# Fine-grained GitHub PAT scoped to Joeareval19/VCP-WebPage, with
# Issues: Read and write + Contents: Read-only. Used by api/file-feedback.js
# to file the extracted scope of work as a Pending ticket. A classic PAT
# with `gist`+`repo` scopes is no longer required now that transcript
# storage moved to Supabase (see SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY below) instead
# of a secret Gist. Deliberately separate from any token used by the
# agent-dispatch pipeline (agent-dispatch/README.md).
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# Supabase SERVICE ROLE key (not the anon/publishable key) for the vcp-ops
# project (qaorlbgrkpldcatyntlw) — used by api/file-feedback.js to write
# full session records to vcp_voice_sessions (schema from #52/#53) and to
# update filed_issue after a ticket is filed. The anon key cannot be used
# here: vcp_voice_sessions' RLS policy is INSERT-only for anon (no
# select/update/delete), and this endpoint needs to UPDATE filed_issue
# after filing. Get this from the Supabase dashboard's Project Settings ->
# API -> service_role key — treat it as a full-access database credential,
# never expose it client-side.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
